ther%20nations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fthey-charge-a-lot-donald-trump-threatens-reciprocal-tariffs-against-india%2Farticleshow%2F116417313.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fthey-charge-a-lot-donald-trump-threatens-reciprocal-tariffs-against-india%2Famp_articleshow%2F116417313.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fthey-charge-a-lot-donald-trump-threatens-reciprocal-tariffs-against-india%2Famp_articleshow%2F116417313.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Russian%20Law%20Will%20Remove%20Taliban's%20%26quot%3BTerrorist%26quot%3B%20Label%2C%20HTS%20Could%20Be%20Next%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20parliament%20has%20passed%20a%20law%20that%20would%20allow%20courts%20to%20suspend%20bans%20on%20groups%20designated%20as%20terrorist%20organisations%20by%20Moscow.%20The%20new%20law%2C%20passed%20by%20parliament's%20lower%20house%2C%20the%20State%20Duma%2C%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20Moscow%20to%20normalise%20ties%20with%20the%20Afghan%20Taliban%20and%20potentially%20with%20the%20new%20leadership%20of%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20outlines%20a%20legal%20mechanism%20for%20groups%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20country's%20official%20banned%20list%20of%20outlawed%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%26quot%3B%20organisations%20by%20order%20of%20a%20court%20if%20they%20cease%20terrorist-related%20activity.%20Under%20the%20law%2C%20Russia's%20Prosecutor%20General%20could%20file%20a%20request%20with%20a%20court%20outlining%20that%20a%20banned%20group%20has%20%26quot%3Bceased%26quot%3B%20its%20activities%20%26quot%3Bin%20support%20of%20terrorism.%26quot%3B%20A%20judge%20could%20then%20rule%20to%20remove%20the%20designation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20was%20in%20the%20first%20batch%20of%20groups%20to%20be%20added%20to%20the%20banned%20list%2C%20in%20February%202003%2C%20and%20Syria's%20HTS%20was%20added%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20has%20been%20courting%20relations%20with%20the%20Taliban%20after%20the%20Islamist%20group%20seized%20power%20in%20August%202021%20as%20US-led%20forces%20staged%20a%20chaotic%20withdrawal%20after%2020%20years%20of%20war.%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20in%20July%20that%20the%20Taliban%20was%20now%20an%20ally%20in%20fighting%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Taliban's%20expected%20removal%20from%20Russia's%20terrorist%20registry%20would%20not%20amount%20to%20a%20formal%20recognition%20of%20its%20government%2C%20or%20what%20it%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3BIslamic%20Emirate%20of%20Afghanistan%26quot%3B%20-%20a%20move%20no%20country%20in%20the%20world%20has%20yet%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20calls%20in%20Moscow%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20Syrian%20group%20Hayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%20(HTS)--that%20spearheaded%20the%20toppling%20of%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20this%20month--%20from%20Moscow's%20list%20of%20banned%20terror%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20Russia's%20Muslim%20region%20of%20Chechnya%2C%20Ramzan%20Kadyrov%2C%20on%20Monday%20said%20Russia%20needed%20ties%20to%20the%20new%20Syrian%20authorities%20to%20ensure%20stability%20and%20prevent%20a%20humanitarian%20catastrophe.%20Kadyrov%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20close%20Putin%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia's%20Stake%20In%20Syria%20And%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20sees%20a%20major%20security%20threat%20from%20Islamist%20militant%20groups%20based%20in%20a%20string%20of%20countries%20from%20Afghanistan%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20where%20Russia%20lost%20a%20major%20ally%20with%20the%20fall%20of%20Assad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20toppling%20of%20the%20Assad%20regime%20threatens%20the%20end%20of%20Russia's%20presence%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20its%20coveted%20military%20foothold%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20region--%20the%20naval%20base%20of%20Tartus%20and%2C%20further%20north%2C%20the%20Hmeimim%20Air%20Base%2C%20both%20with%2049-year-leases%20received%20after%20Russia%20helped%20to%20save%20Assad's%20regime%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20has%20used%20these%20bases%20to%20challenge%20American%20supremacy%20by%20projecting%20its%20military%20power%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20and%20claiming%20the%20role%20of%20a%20world%20power%20with%20vital%20regional%20interests.%20With%20the%20end%20of%20the%20friendly%20regime%2C%20Russia's%20military%20foothold%20in%20the%20Mediterranean%20is%20threatened%2C%20but%20this%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20Moscow%20is%20about%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%2C%20this%20week%2C%20said%20that%20Moscow%20was%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20new%20leadership%20in%20Syria%2C%20where%20it%20hopes%20to%20retain%20the%20use%20of%20an%20airfield%20and%20a%20naval%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20also%20has%20a%20complex%20and%20bloodstained%20history%20in%20Afghanistan.%20Soviet%20troops%20invaded%20the%20country%20in%20December%201979%20to%20prop%20up%20a%20Communist%20government%20but%20became%20bogged%20down%20in%20a%20long%20war%20against%20mujahideen%20fighters%20armed%20by%20the%20United%20States.%20Soviet%20leader%20Mikhail%20Gorbachev%20pulled%20his%20army%20out%20in%201989%2C%20by%20which%20time%20some%2015%2C000%20Soviet%20soldiers%20had%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20gunmen%20killed%20145%20people%20at%20a%20concert%20hall%20outside%20Moscow%20in%20an%20attack%20claimed%20by%20Islamic%20State.%20US%20officials%20said%20they%20had%20intelligence%20indicating%20it%20was%20the%20Afghan%20branch%20of%20the%20group%2C%20Islamic%20State%20Khorasan%20(ISIS-K)%2C%20that%20was%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20now%20the%20Taliban%20says%20it%20is%20working%20to%20wipe%20out%20the%20presence%20of%20Islamic%20State%20in%20Afghanistan.%20But%2C%20Western%20diplomats%20say%20the%20movement's%20path%20towards%20wider%20international%20recognition%20is%20stalled%20until%20it%20changes%20course%20on%20women's%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20has%20closed%20high%20schools%20and%20universities%20to%20girls%20and%20women%20and%20placed%20restrictions%20on%20their%20movement%20without%20a%20male%20guardian.%20It%20says%20it%20respects%20women's%20rights%20in%20line%20with%20its%20strict%20interpretation%20of%20Islamic%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734488580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fdhh0nq6k_vladimir-putin-reuters_625x300_29_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussias-new-law-to-recognise-taliban-potentially-syrias-hayatal-sham-7273734%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Russian%20parliament%20has%20passed%20a%20law%20that%20would%20allow%20courts%20to%20suspend%20bans%20on%20groups%20designated%20as%20terrorist%20organisations%20by%20Moscow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussias-new-law-to-recognise-taliban-potentially-syrias-hayatal-sham-7273734%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Walmart's%20Flipkart%20has%20a%20tough%20battle%20ahead%20in%20India%2C%20a%202026%20IPO%20likely%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734488444000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fwalmart-s-flipkart-has-a-tough-battle-ahead-in-india-a-2026-ipo-likely-124121800121_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Flipkart%20is%20a%20stake%20Walmart%20has%20put%20down%20in%20a%20market%20where%20brick-and-mortar%20foreign%20retailers%20face%20stifling%20restrictions%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-stan