in%20Ohio%20data%20centers%2C%20Ohio%20Gov.%20Mike%20DeWine%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20will%20consider%20locations%20outside%20its%20power-strained%20hub%20in%20Columbus.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20exchange%20for%20tax%20credits%2C%20Amazon%20committed%20to%20more%20than%201%2C000%20new%20jobs%20in%20its%20Ohio%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20committed%20to%20spending%20%2410%20billion%20on%20the%20expansion%20of%20its%20Ohio%20data%20center%20operations%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20billions%20of%20dollars%20it%20has%20already%20said%20it%20plans%20to%20spend%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Ohio%20Gov.%20Mike%20DeWine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgovernor.ohio.gov%2Fmedia%2Fnews-and-media%2Fgovernor-dewine-announces-10-billion-investment-plan-from-amazon-web-services-in-greater-ohio%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20giant's%20new%20Ohio%20facilities%2C%20which%20should%20be%20completed%20by%20the%20end%20of%202030%2C%20will%20help%20power%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-data-centers-delays-costs-power-labor-shortages-aws-ai-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20into%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20its%20cloud%20computing%20unit%2C%20Amazon%20Web%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20last%20year%2C%20AWS%20said%20it%20would%20invest%20%247.8%20billion%20to%20expand%20its%20data%20center%20hub%20in%20Columbus%20and%20the%20surrounding%20suburbs.%20The%20company%20started%20building%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20region%20in%202015%20and%20has%20at%20least%20six%20different%20campuses%20that%20are%20either%20operational%20or%20under%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOhio%20has%20committed%20to%20spending%20more%20than%20%2423%20billion%20on%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20state%20between%20the%20money%20it%20has%20already%20spent%20and%20its%20committed%20investments%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Ohio's%20Department%20of%20Development%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investment%20in%20Ohio%20is%20part%20of%20Amazon's%20aggressive%20spending%20plan%20on%20data%20center%20construction%20to%20support%20AI%20demand.%20Amazon%20%3Cspan%3ECEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20said%20on%20the%20company's%20third-quarter%20earnings%20call%20in%20October%20that%20it%20plans%20to%20spend%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ceo-andy-jassy-even-more-bullish-ai-cloud-opportunity-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%2475%20billion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0on%20capital%20expenditures%20in%202024%2C%20most%20of%20which%20will%20go%20to%20cloud%20computing%20and%20data%20centers%2C%20and%20it%20expects%20to%20spend%20even%20more%20next%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20politicians%20have%20dubbed%20the%20Central%20Ohio%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Silicon%20Heartland.%26quot%3B%20Gov.%20DeWine%20touted%20the%20AWS%20announcement%20this%20week%20as%20%26quot%3Bstrengthening%20the%20state's%20role%20as%20a%20major%20technology%20hub.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirginia-data-center-boom-power-grid-utility-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20located%20in%20Northern%20Virginia%2C%20the%20largest%20data%20center%20market%20in%20the%20world.%20That%20area%20has%20become%20saturated%20with%20new%20facilities%20waiting%20to%20be%20connected%20to%20the%20electric%20grid.%20In%20the%20last%2018%20months%2C%20Amazon%20and%20its%20competitors%20have%20announced%20plans%20to%20build%20data%20centers%20in%20states%20nationwide.%20Just%20this%20year%2C%20Amazon%20announced%20plans%20to%20spend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Faws%2Faws-indiana-investment-11-billion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2411%20billion%20on%20data%20centers%20in%20Indiana%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmississippi.org%2Fnews%2Famazon-web-services-to-invest-record-shattering-10-billion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2410%20billion%20in%20Mississippi%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f908702-7682-4785-ab0c-804a38ff9faa%5C%22%3EJob%20creation%20in%20Ohio%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOhio%2C%20which%20offers%20a%20generous%20slate%20of%20state%20and%20local%20tax%20incentives%2C%20including%20an%20up%20to%20100%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jobsohio.com%2Fprograms-services%2Fincentives%2Fdata-center-tax-exemption%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esales%20and%20use%20tax%20exemption%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20data%20center%20equipment%2C%20has%20seen%20a%20sharp%20uptick%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20latest%20investment%2C%20the%20Ohio%20Tax%20Credit%20Authority%20approved%20additional%20job%20creation%20tax%20credits%20in%20AWS's%20existing%20economic%20development%20agreement%20with%20the%20state.%20In%20exchange%20for%20annual%20job%20creation%20tax%20credits%2C%20AWS%20has%20promised%201%2C058%20%26quot%3Bfull-time%20equivalent%26quot%3B%20jobs%20with%20a%20minimum%20average%20annual%20payroll%20of%20%24101.37%20million%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Ohio's%20Department%20of%20Development%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcodes.ohio.gov%2Fohio-revised-code%2Fsection-122.17%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOhio%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20defines%20%26quot%3Bfull-time%20equivalent%20employees%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20result%20of%20a%20calculation%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bdividing%20the%20total%20number%20of%20hours%20for%20which%20employees%20were%20compensated%20for%20employment%20in%20the%20project%20by%20two%20thousand%20eighty.%26quot%3B%20The%20employees%20must%20be%20directly%20employed%20by%20Amazon%20for%20the%20company%20to%20receive%20its%20tax%20credits%2C%20although%20there%20is%20no%20requirement%20for%20the%20kinds%20of%20jobs%20Amazon%20must%20offer.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20BI%20contacted%20AWS%20and%20asked%20what%20types%20of%20jobs%20would%20be%20available%20in%20its%20new%20Ohio%20data%20centers%2C%20an%20AWS%20spokesperson%20reiterated%20the%20information%20listed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globenewswire.com%2Fnews-release%2F2024%2F12%2F16%2F2997684%2F0%2Fen%2FGovernor-DeWine-Announces-10-Billion-Investment-Plan-from-Amazon-Web-Services-in-Greater-Ohio.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGov.%20DeWine's%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20referred%20to%20the%20jobs%20as%20%26quot%3Bnew%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwell-paying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273009ae5-5054-41f6-a0bd-6572a62e33f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EElectricity%20demand%20rises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAWS's%20financial%20commitment%20to%20the%20state%20will%20hinge%20on%20whether%20local%20utilities%20can%20provide%20the%20amount%20of%20electricity%20the%20company%20eventually%20says%20it%20will%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAEP%20Ohio%2C%20the%20Columbus%20utility%20that%20serves%20Amazon%2C%20said%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20it%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faep-ohio-data-centers-pay-for-electricity-demand-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%20gigawatts%20of%20service%20requests%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20data%20centers%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20an%20amount%20that%20would%20put%20the%20region's%20demand%20for%20electricity%20close%20to%20New%20York%20City's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20that%20demand%20comes%20from%20the%20wealthy%20suburban%20enclave%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-ai-artificial-intelligence-farmland-power-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Albany%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ohio%2C%20where%20Meta%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20QTS%20are%20all%20constructing%20major%20data%20center%20projects.%20The%20site%20of%20Intel's%20future%20semiconductor%20chip%20plant%20is%20in%20neighboring%20Johnstown%2C%20Ohio.%20The%20New%20Albany%20Company%2C%20the%20real%20estate%20company%20founded%20by%20billionaire%20retail%20mogul%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvictorias-secret-parent-company-ceo-designed-ohio-town-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELes%20Wexner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20orchestrated%20many%20of%20the%20area's%20major%20land%20sales%20to%20tech%20companies%2C%20including%20Intel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20newest%20data%20centers%2C%20AWS%20will%20look%20to%20sites%20beyond%20the%20Columbus%20region%2C%20though%20no%20locations%20have%20been%20finalized%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20from%20Gov.%20DeWine's%20office.%20If%20AWS%20locates%20a%20data%20center%20outside%20the%20Columbus%20region%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20outside%20AEP's%20service%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAEP%20has%20asked%20Ohio's%20public%20utilities%20regulator%20to%20approve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdis.puc.state.oh.us%2FDocumentRecord.aspx%3FDocID%3D16943d1f-cf13-4b6a-97ec-d1de2521d5ba%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20tariff%20and%20a%20special%20rate%20class%20for%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20require%20the%20power-hungry%20facilities%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20electricity%20they%20anticipate%20needing%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20ultimately%20do%20not%20consume%20all%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20center%20industry%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20is%20working%20to%20quash%20AEP's%20proposal.%20In%20a%20November%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdis.puc.state.oh.us%2FDocumentRecord.aspx%3FDocID%3De8fca26d-906c-4d34-8fef-b213ad69966f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestimony%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0filed%20with%20the%20Public%20Utilities%20Commission%20of%20Ohio%2C%20Michael%20Fradette%2C%20who%20leads%20Amazon's%20energy%20strategy%2C%20called%20the%20proposal%20a%20%26quot%3Bdiscriminatory%20structure%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bunfairly%20targets%20data%20center%20customers%20by%20targeting%20customers%20in%20specific%20industries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20has%20sowed%20division%20among%20corporate%20interests%20in%20Ohio.%20Those%20who%20oppose%20the%20tariffs%20include%20the%20Ohio%20Manufacturers'%20Association%20Energy%20Group%2C%20a%20lobbying%20offshoot%20of%20the%20state's%20major%20manufacturing%20industry%20trade%20group%2C%20and%20the%20Ohio%20Energy%20Leadership%20Council%2C%20which%20is%20represented%20by%20David%20Proa%C3%B1o%2C%20a%20lawyer%20in%20BakerHostetler's%20Columbus%20office%20who%20also%20represents%20Amazon's%20data%20center%20business%20before%20the%20Public%20Utilities%20Commission%20of%20Ohio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Ohio%20Energy%20Group%2C%20which%20counts%20Cargill%2C%20Ford%2C%20GE%2C%20and%20Intel%20as%20members%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdis.puc.state.oh.us%2FDocumentRecord.aspx%3FDocID%3D9b0008f4-8ead-4821-a475-4d966c4cdf10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestified%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20favor%20of%20AEP's%20proposed%20data%20center%20tariffs.%20Walmart%2C%20a%20large%20customer%20of%20AEP%20in%20Ohio%2C%20has%20also%20come%20out%20supporting%20the%20tariff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAEP%20is%20planning%20new%20transmission%20infrastructure%20projects%20to%20service%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20Columbus%20area%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Intel%20chip%20plant.%20The%20future%20of%20the%20chip%20plant%2C%20which%20is%20supposed%20to%20bring%203%2C000%20advanced%20manufacturing%20jobs%20to%20central%20Ohio%2C%20is%20uncertain%20as%20the%20company%20debates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceos-discuss-splitting-product-from-manufacturing-businesses-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espinning%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20struggling%20foundry%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20energy%20demand%20from%20Columbus%20area%20data%20centers%20has%20triggered%20the%20need%20for%20new%20transmission%20infrastructure.%20Under%20AEP's%20existing%20rate%20st