%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20charges%20of%20first-degree%20murder%2C%20with%20prosecutors%20alleging%20he%20killed%20UnitedHealthcare%20CEO%20Brian%20Thompson%20%26quot%3Bin%20furtherance%20of%20terrorism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20have%20also%20accused%20Mangione%20of%20second-degree%20murder%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20slew%20of%20counts%20related%20to%20the%20possession%20of%20an%20illegal%20%26quot%3Bghost%20gun%26quot%3B%20made%20from%203D-printed%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20five-day%20manhunt%2C%20Mangione%20was%20arrested%20last%20week%20at%20a%20restaurant%20in%20Altoona%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20on%20gun%20and%20false%20ID%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20say%20he%20killed%20Thompson%20outside%20a%20midtown%20Manhattan%20hotel%20on%20December%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20killing%20was%20intended%20to%20invoke%20terror%2C%26quot%3B%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20Tuesday%20afternoon%2C%20calling%20it%20a%26quot%3Bbrazen%2C%20targeted%20and%20premeditated%20shooting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20offered%20a%20detailed%20look%20at%20Mangione's%20movements%20Tuesday.%20They%20say%20he%20stayed%20at%20an%20Upper%20West%20Side%20hostel%20for%20more%20than%20a%20week%2C%20using%20a%20fake%20New%20Jersey%20ID%2C%20before%20carrying%20out%20the%20killing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20prosecutors%2C%20two%20of%20the%20shell%20casings%20for%20the%20bullets%20that%20killed%20Thompson%20had%20the%20words%20%26quot%3BDENY%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BDEPOSE%26quot%3B%20written%20on%20them.%20The%20word%20%26quot%3BDELAY%26quot%3B%20was%20written%20on%20a%20bullet%20found%20at%20the%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20arrest%20warrant%20previously%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20indicated%20that%20Mangione%20would%20be%20charged%20with%20second-degree%20murder%20along%20with%20four%20other%20charges%20related%20to%20illegal%20weapon%20possession.%20The%20first-degree%20murder%20charge%20reflects%20a%20more%20severe%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Mangione%2C%2026%2C%20is%20convicted%20of%20the%20first-degree%20murder%20charge%2C%20he%20could%20spend%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%20in%20prison%20without%20parole.%20The%20charge%2C%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20commit%20terrorism%2C%20refers%20to%20a%20killing%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bintended%20to%20intimidate%20or%20coerce%20a%20civilian%20population%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Binfluence%20the%20policies%20of%20a%20unit%20of%20government%20by%20intimidation%20or%20coercion%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMangione%20has%20not%20yet%20entered%20a%20plea%20for%20any%20of%20the%20charges%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20minimum%20required%20sentence%20for%20first-degree%20murder%2C%2025%20to%20life%2C%20would%20mean%20Mangione%20would%20not%20see%20a%20parole%20officer%20until%20age%2051.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20charge%20could%20become%20a%20bargaining%20chip%20for%20Bragg%2C%20former%20Manhattan%20prosecutor%20Michael%20Bachner%2C%20who%20is%20now%20in%20private%20practice%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20risk%20now%20of%20a%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20life%20without%20the%20possibility%20parole%2C%20that%20top%20terrorism%20count%20may%20induce%20the%20defendant%20to%20enter%20a%20plea%2C%20if%20one%20is%20offered%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jessica%20Tisch%2C%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Police%20Commissioner%2C%20and%20Alvin%20Bragg%2C%20Manhattan%20DA%2C%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20announcing%20indictment%20of%20Mangione.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6761e5421d90e3bcf31d706f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EManhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20announces%20Luigi%20Mangione's%20murder%20indictment%2C%20flanked%20by%20NYPD%20Commissioner%20Jessica%20Tisch%20and